(Translated by Google) In the style of proximity, it does not make the best. An undeniable advantage of this resort is the proximity of the Jean-Talon Market. If you want, on the contrary, restaurants, there is a panoply for all budgets to the west. The visit of St-Hubert Street also started at this station.

(Translated by Google) Probably the most mixing station on the network at the level of the exits to the outside. I've been there about 20 times and still get lost. Well located on the other hand.

(Original)
Probablement la station la plus mélangeante du réseau au niveau des sorties vers l'extérieur. J'y suis allé une vingtaine de fois et je me perd encore toujours. Bien situé par contre.

(Translated by Google) Finally there is an elevator which goes up to the exits. Before there is only to go to the docks. Clean and well organized. Except that I went to see someone for a lost card and she couldn't do anything. I had to go to Berri. Well located. Near Jean-Talon Market, near other shops and restaurants / cafes. Near Plaza Saint-Hubert.

(Original)
Enfin il y a ascenseur qui monte jusqu'aux sorties. Avant il y a que pour aller aux quais. Propre et bien organisé. Sauf que je suis allée voir quelqu'un pour une carte perdue et elle pouvait pas rien faire. J'ai dû aller a Berri. Bien située. Près du Marché Jean-Talon, près autres commerces et restos/cafés. Près Plaza Saint-Hubert.

(Translated by Google) Station centrale pour accéder au grand marche couvert et publique du marché Jean talon.
Accessibility to go up and down the stairs with the elevators that were installed in 2018 after months and months of work.
Now it is easy to go on the roads St Denis and Lajeunesse.

Accesibilidad para subir y bajar las escaleras con los ascensores qué fueran instalado en 2018 después mes y meses de trabajos.

(Translated by Google) Management of pitiful work. The junction line blue / orange is catastrophic, years that it lasts ... we must pay to undergo it ????

(Original)

(Translated by Google) It's a metro ... what more can we say! We don't put ourselves in Paris or New York.
Clean for public transport. Super convenient for getting around Montreal quickly.
There will always be something to improve but in principle nothing negative to complain about.

(Original)
C’est un métro... que dire de plus! On se mettre pas plus qu’à Paris ou New-York.
Propre pour un transport en commun. Super pratique pour se déplacer rapidement dans Montréal.
Il y aura toujours de quoi améliorer mais dans le principe rien de négatif à redire.

(Original)

(Translated by Google) Blue line docks well indicated, clean, kind and smiling staff, several strategic exits well positioned and indicated.
New service center intelligently redesigned.

(Original)
Quais de la ligne bleue biens indiqué, propre, personel gentil et souriant, plusieurs sorties stratégiques bien positionné et indiqué.
Nouveau centre de service repensé intelligemment.

(Translated by Google) Very good everyday resort. But do not expect more. It is not the station for major events.

(Original)
Très bonne station de tous les jours. Mais il ne faut pas s'attendre à plus. Ce n'est pas la station des grands événements.

(Translated by Google) The correspondence between the 2 lines is done well. Clean station.

(Original)
La correspondance entre les 2 lignes se fait bien. Station propre.

(Translated by Google) Important metro station.

Jean-Talon station is a hotspot in the metro. The Orange (North / South) and Blue (East / West) lines cross at this station.

At the exit, there are several stores ... grocery store, pharmacy, restaurants, etc ... And you can also take the bus on Jean-Talon Street to the East and West.

And a few blocks east, there is the northern beginning of Plaza St-Hubert.

(Original)
Station de métro importante.

Le station Jean-Talon est un point névralgique dans le métro.  Les lignes Orange (Nord/Sud)et Bleue (Est/Ouest) se croisent à cette station.

À la sortie, il y a plusieurs magasins... épicerie, pharmacie, restaurants, etc... Et on peut aussi prendre l'autobus sur la rue Jean-Talon vers l'Est et l'Ouest.

Et à quelques coins de rue vers l'Est, il y a le début nord de la Plaza St-Hubert.
